  "title": "Operations Executive",
  "description": "<p><br /></p><p>Location: Tai Seng</p><p>Working Schedule: 5 days work week</p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><p>•\tCoordinate vehicle inspections and the timely renewal of road tax, insurance, COE, and LM certificates in compliance with Singapore regulations.</p><p>•\tMaintain comprehensive and up-to-date records of vehicle registration, road tax, insurance coverage, and inspection schedules.</p><p>•\tManage the purchase and administration of Vehicle Parking Coupons (VPC) and apply for oversize vehicle permits where required.</p><p>•\tCoordinate vehicle acquisition, disposal, scrapping, and deregistration processes, liaising with appointed agents and relevant service providers.</p><p>•\tArrange and monitor vehicle repairs, maintenance, and servicing schedules, and liaise with workshops and service providers to ensure timely and cost-effective completion.</p><p>•\tTrack, monitor, and control expenses related to fuel, repairs, maintenance, toll charges, and insurance premiums.</p><p>•\tProvide accident assistance by coordinating with workshops and insurance brokers, including follow-up on claims and documentation.</p><p>•\tVehicle insurance renewal and maintain proper documentation and records for audit and reference purposes.</p><p>•\tVerify supplier invoices and ensure all supporting quotations and documents are duly attached prior to processing.</p><p>•\tPrepare, raise, and control internal documentation for vehicle disposal and deregistration.</p><p>•\tEnsure proper control and safekeeping of company car keys, maintaining accurate access and usage records in accordance with company policies.</p><p>•\tAdminister petrol and diesel card applications and replacements</p><p>•\tManage ERP card issuance, purchase, and refund processes, ensuring accurate tracking and reconciliation.</p><p>•\tEnsure full compliance with transport regulations, licensing requirements, and statutory obligations.</p><p>•\tPerform additional administrative and operational duties as assigned to support overall business operations.</p><p>Requirements:</p><p>•\tDiploma holders</p><p>•\tMinimum 3 years of relevant experience</p><p>•\tKnowledge in Microsoft Office</p>",
